106 Alas, my conversion was late;
107 but, as soon as I became the Roman shepherd,
108 I uncovered the deceitful life.

109 I saw that the heart found no peace there,
110 nor could one ascend any higher in that life;
111 wherefore love for this life was kindled in me.

112 Up to that point I was a wretched soul,
113 separated from God, altogether avaricious;
114 now, as you see, I am punished for it here.

115 What avarice does is declared here
